record_data.record_plain_text: EcoGrove Wind LLC FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF NO. 1 1. Availability. EcoGrove Wind LLC ("Seller") makes energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale, except as prohibited in 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, Section 35.39(b). 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all of Seller's sales of energy and capacity not otherwise subject to a particular tariff of Seller. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at the rates established between the purchaser and the Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller has requested and been granted the following waivers of Commission regulations, pursuant to a Letter Order issued by the Commission in Docket No. ER09-554-000: (a) authorization for sales of energy at market-based rates; (b) waiver of the filing requirements of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, 18 C.F.R. Part 35 (except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16); (c) waiver of the accounting , reporting and other requirements of 18 C.F.R. Parts 41 (accounts, records and memoranda), 101 (uniform system of accounts) and 141 (statement and reports); (d) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act and 18 C.F.R. Part 34 for any future securities or debt issuances or assumption of liabilities by Seller; and (e) such other waivers and authorizations as the Commission may deem appropriate. 7. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). 8. Effective Date. This Tariff is effective March 11, 2009.

record_data.record_plain_text: COTENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT by and among EcoGrove Wind LLC, an Illinois limited liability company, High Point Solar LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, and Acciona Energy USA Global LLC, a Delaware limited liability company September 1, 2021 Cotenancy and Shared Facililies Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC) COTENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT This COTENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this "Agreement") is made and entered into as of September I, 2021 (the "Effective Date") by and among EcoGrove Wind LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("EcoGrove"), High Point Solar LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("High Point" and, together with EcoGrove, the "Owners"), and Acciona Energy USA Global LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (the "Shared Facilities Manager"). Capitalized terms used herein and not otherwise defined shall have the meaning assigned thereto in Appendix I attached hereto and hereby made a part hereof. RECITALS A. EcoGrove has developed, owns and operates a wind energy generating facility having approximately 100.5 MW nameplate generating capacity located in Stephenson County, Illinois, known as the "EcoGrove Wind Farm" (the "EcoGrove Project"),and High Point is developing a solar photovoltaic generating facility having approximately 100 MW nameplate generating capacity located in Stephenson County, Illinois, and neighboring or adjacent to the EcoGrove Project, known as the "High Point Solar Project" (the "High Point Project"). B. The Owners have determined that certain assets and facilities developed, owned and operated by EcoGrove in connection with the EcoGrove Project, including, without limitation, substation, generation tie line and other interconnection facilities, and certain assets and facilities planned for development by High Point in connection with the High Point Project, may be used or useful in connection with the operation of both Projects, and have agreed that mutual benefits and efficiencies can be obtained by their jointly owning and sharing use of certain assets, facilities and premises (hereinafter more particularly defined as the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, respectively), and sharing certain costs and expenses related thereto (hereinafter more particularly defined as the Shared Expenses), and Shared Facilities Manager has agreed to perform certain services with respect thereto. C. The Owners and Shared Facilities Manager desire to set forth their respective rights and obligations with respect to the Shared Facilities, the Shared Premises and the Shared Expenses, as provided in this Agreement. D. The Owners and Shared Facilities Manager acknowledge and agree that this Agreement is (i) the "Shared Facilities Agreement" referenced in Schedule F to the Interconnection Agreement for the High Point Project and (ii) the "Shared Facilities Agreement" referenced in Schedule F of the amendment to the Interconnection Agreement for the EcoGrove Project. NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing recitals, the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged by the parties hereto, the Parties agree as follows: 1. SHARED FACILITIES AND SHARED PREMISES. Page I Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC) 4853 2776-3956.5 1.1 Transfers and Interests. 1. 1. 1 On the Transfer Date, for and in consideration of High Point's payment to EcoGrove of the Shared Facilities Payment, EcoGrove shall Transfer to High Point a portion of its right, title and interest in and to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises such that each of EcoGrove and High Point shall have an undivided interest, as tenants in common, in and to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises so Transferred in an amount equal to its respective Project Percentage Interest. Such Transfer of an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities shall be effected and documented by the Shared Facilities Bill of Sale, which will be executed by the Owners effective as of the Transfer Date. Such Transfer of an undivided interest in the Shared Premises shall be effected and documented by the Shared Fee Premises Deed, with respect to the Shared Fee Premises, and by the Shared Premises Agreements Assignment, with respect to the other Shared Premises, which instruments will be executed by the Owners effective as of the Transfer Date and recorded. 1.1.2 From and following the Transfer Date, High Point shall have the right to enter upon the Shared Fee Premises for purposes of constructing the Warehouse Storage Building. Upon completion of the Warehouse Storage Building to the reasonable satisfaction of EcoGrove, EcoGrove shall pay to High Point the Warehouse Storage Building Payment and High Point shall transfer to EcoGrove a portion of its right, title and interest in and to the Warehouse Storage Building such that each of EcoGrove and High Point shall have an undivided interest, as tenants in common, in and to the Warehouse Storage Building in an amount equal to its respective Project Percentage Interest. Such Transfer of an undivided interest in the Warehouse Storage Building shall be effected and documented by the Warehouse Storage Building Bill of Sale, which will be executed by the Owners effective as of the date of such payment, whereupon the Warehouse Storage Building shall be included among the Shared Facilities. 1.2 Rights and Obligations.Subject to the other requirements of this Agreement, each Owner shall have the right and obligation to share the benefits, costs and liabilities of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises to the extent of its Project Percentage Interest in such Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. Subject to the foregoing, the Owners will agree to mutually satisfactory arrangements for their cooperative use of the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises. Each Owner agrees that, as between such Owner and the respective fee owners of the Shared Premises, other than the Shared Fee Premises, such Owner's use of the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises shall be pursuant to and subject to the terms and conditions of its own respective interest in the Shared Premises and the Shared Premises Agreements for the Shared Premises. 2. SHARED EXPENSES. 2.1 Owner Responsibility.Each Owner, severally but not jointly, shall be responsible for and shall pay its Project Percentage Interest of the expenses and liabilities relating to the ownership, operation, maintenance, repair and inspection of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in which it has an interest (the "Shared Expenses")which are not within the scope of the Project O&M Agreements, but which are intended by the Owners to be shared among all Projects. Page 2 Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Poin1 Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956.5 The Shared Facilities Manager, as authorized agent for each Owner, shall administer the invoicing, collection and payment of the Shared Expenses. Included Expenses. The Shared Expenses include, without limitation, (i) expenses and liabilities arising under any Shared Facilities O&M Agreement, (ii) expenses and liabilities arising under any Shared Premises Agreements or otherwise due to landowners on account of the Shared Facilities, and (iii) other expenses and liabilities incurred by or otherwise allocable to Shared Facilities Manager hereunder related to the use, maintenance, repair and inspection of the Shared Premises. For the avoidance of doubt, Shared Expenses shall not include any expense with respect to damage to the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises arising from the actions or inactions (including negligence or breach of this Agreement) of an Owner, which shall be paid solely by such Owner. Nor shall Shared Expenses include reimbursement for expenses that duplicate amounts paid to the Shared Facilities Manager under any other agreement, including any O&M Agreement. The Owners from time to time may designate in writing additional expenses as Shared Expenses to be administered by the Shared Facilities Manager hereunder. 2.3 Liabilities for the Account of the Owners. Except as specifically set forth in this Agreement, each Owner shall be solely responsible for its Liabilities relating to its Project and Project Specific Assets, including without limitation, all Liabilities arising from acquiring, designing, installing, constructing, using, operating, maintaining and repairing its Project Specific Assets, and each Owner shall, at its sole cost and expense, maintain in good working order and repair at all times each part of its Project that connects with, will connect with, or affects the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the cost and expense of any Project Specific Assets and the connection and integration of Project Specific Assets with any Shared Facilities (including without limitation, any design, procurement, construction, or installation costs) shall not be considered Shared Expenses hereunder, and shall be borne solely by the applicable Owner that owns such Project Specific Assets. In addition, each Owner shall be individually responsible for any fees, expenses or liabilities incurred by or otherwise allocable to Shared Facilities Manager for the construction, use, maintenance, operation, repair, and inspection of any incremental equipment added to the Shared Facilities, as applicable, for the purpose of accommodating the interconnection of such Owner's Project. Each Owner shall be responsible for all Liabilities arising from such Owner's actions or inactions in violation of this Agreement. 2.4 Invoicing: Late Payments. No later than the first day of each calendar month, the Shared Facilities Manager shall invoice such Owner for its respective portions of the Shared Expenses for the prior month. The Shared Facilities Manager's invoice shall include a detailed breakdown of the Shared Expenses and each Owner's share of the Shared Expenses, along with wire transfer instructions for making payment to Shared Facilities Manager. The Owners shall make all payments to Shared Facilities Manager (or directly to the other Owners to whom the Shared Expenses may be payable) under this Section 2.4 by wire transfer of immediately available funds as provided in the Shared Facilities Manager's invoice within thirty (30) days of receipt of such invoice. All sums not paid within thirty (30) days after receipt of Shared Facilities Manager's invoice shall thereafter bear interest at the Default Rate. Each Owner will have the right to audit, and receive supporting documentation for, any expenses or other amounts required to be paid by Page 3 Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956.5 such Owner under this Agreement. If there is a dispute as to any amount invoiced by Shared Facilities Manager, the Owners shall pay all amounts not in dispute in accordance with this Section 2.4. The Owners shall pay any disputed amount ultimately determined as payable with interest thereon at the Default Rate accruing from the date of receipt of the Shared Facilities Manager's disputed invoice. 2.5 Pre-Invoicing. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right to pre-invoice the Owners for their Project Percentage Interest of any reasonably anticipated expenses to be paid or materials and components to be provided hereunder, and to not proceed with the payment or acquisition of such materials and components, as applicable, unless payment has been received by the Shared Facilities Manager therefor. 3. TERM. 3. l Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date, and, unless sooner terminated by mutual agreement of the Owners or the consolidation of ownership of the Shared Facilities and rights of the Owners in and to the Shared Premises in a single Owner, shall continue through the sixtieth (60th) anniversary of the Effective Date. 3.2 Elective Termination at Project Decommissioning.Notwithstanding the foregoing, either Owner may elect to terminate this Agreement in connection with the permanent cessation of operations for its respective Project, by giving written notice to the other Owner at least one hundred eighty (180) days prior to such Owner's proposed termination date. Unless the other Owner receiving such notice agrees in writing to the joint termination of this Agreement as of such proposed termination date, the terminating Owner shall deliver to the non-terminating Owner, on or before the proposed termination date, (i) transfer instruments, in form reasonably acceptable to the non-terminating Owner, conveying to the non-terminating Owner all of the terminating Owner's right, title and interest in and to the Shared Facilities, the Shared Premises and the Shared Premises Agreements (including a special warranty deed conveying the terminating Owner's interest in the Shared Fee Premises), warranting title against any claim arising by, through or under the terminating Owner other than those arising under both Owners jointly or consented to in writing by the non-terminating Owner, and (ii) an amount equal to the terminating Owner's Project Percentage Interest of the estimated costs of removing the Shared Facilities from the Shared Premises and restoring the Shared Premises to the condition required under the Shared Premises Agreements, net of salvage value (including the value of the Transferring Owner's interest in the Shared Fee Premises), in an amount reasonably determined by the Shared Facilities Manager (the "Removal Cost Share"),whereupon this Agreement shall terminate and the non-terminating Owner shall be the sole owner of the Shared Facilities, and the non-terminating Owner shall be solely responsible for costs and expenses of the Shared Facilities accruing after the termination date, including the cost of removal thereof and restoration of the Shared Premises. Upon such termination date and the payment of the Removal Cost Share, this Agreement shall terminate and neither Owner shall have any further obligations hereunder except for those obligations which specifically survive termination. Page4 Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Pomt Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956.5 4. SHARED FACILITIES MANAGER. 4.1 Appointment/Removal/Resignation. The Owners hereby acknowledge the appointment of Acciona Energy USA Global LLC as the initial Shared Facilities Manager. The Shared Facilities Manager may be removed by the Owners at any time upon the written agreement of both Owners and delivery of written notice to the Shared Facilities Manager. The Shared Facilities Manager may resign upon prior written notice to the Owners provided such resignation shall not be effective until the earlier of appointment of a replacement Shared Facilities Manager in accordance with Section 4.2 or forty-five (45) days after receipt by the Owners. 4.2 Appointment of Replacement.Upon resignation or removal of the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to Section 4.1, the consent of both Owners shall be required to appoint a replacement Shared Facilities Manager. 5. OWNER ACCESS AND USE. Use by Projects. Subject to the other requirements of this Agreement, each Owner shall have the right to utilize transmission capacity over the Shared Interconnection Facilities on a firm basis to the extent of its Reserved Capacity. The foregoing rights include use of any electrical transmission lines, transformers, substations, and other electrical components to collect and transmit electricity generated by the Owner's Project over the Shared Facilities to the Point of Interconnection in an amount equal to such Owner's Reserved Capacity. The Owners shall share line losses according to pro rata capacity shares. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, each Owner separately owns and shall own the electrical energy, capacity, and ancillary services generated by, or associated with, its Project. 5.2 Access to Shared Facilities. Each Owner and its Representatives shall have access to the Shared Premises for the installation, maintenance, or repairs of its Project Specific Assets. The Shared Facilities Manager, an Owner and/or any Owner's Representatives shall follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by the agreement of the Owners and Shared Facilities Manager, and shall comply with all applicable Shared Premises Agreements, Laws and Governmental Approvals when on the Shared Premises or accessing the Shared Facilities, except to the extent that following any such rule would violate applicable Law. In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required to access the Shared Facilities to respond to the Emergency, but the Owner shall provide notice of access to Shared Facilities Manager and the other Owner as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter (no more than twenty-four (24) hours after access). 5.3 No Interference. Cooperation and Over-Burdening. An Owner's use of the Shared Facilities and the operation of its Project shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Owner of its respective rights to use the Shared Facilities or the operation of its Project, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Owner hereby consents to the development and operation of each of the Projects owned by the other Owner, and each Owner shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate the other Owner's use of the Shared Facilities for the benefit of the Projects as contemplated by this Agreement. No Owner Page 5 Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956.5 will use or permit the use of the Shared Facilities in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Shared Facilities or any Governmental Approval as to the Shared Facilities or any Project, nor otherwise conduct or permit to be conducted operations on its Project Site which would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Shared Facilities. All incremental costs and expenses associated with an Owner interconnecting a Project into the Shared Facilities shall be for the account of, and paid for, by such Owner. 5.4 Additional Facilities. Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, no Owner shall construct, install or place any additional facilities within the Shared Premises. 5 .5 Conditions to Connecting Projects to the Shared Facilities.Any Owner connecting its Project to the Shared Facilities shall (a) not interfere with the use or access by the other Owner of the Shared Facilities, except as may be necessary during the installation, repair, or replacement of Shared Facilities, (b) to the extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak and/or low generation period any required disconnection of the Shared Facilities to conduct construction activities to minimize the impact on the Project of the other Owner, (c) provide at least thirty (30) days' prior written notice to the other Owner of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, (d) provide at least thirty (30) days' prior written notice to the other Owner of any planned outages, and the durations thereof, of the Shared Facilities that would result in a disconnection of the other Owner's Project, (e) take into consideration, to the extent commercially reasonable, any changes in the construction plans or timing of construction required by the other Owner, (f) be responsible for obtaining and complying with any necessary Governmental Approvals and providing documentary evidence of such ' Governmental Approvals to the other Owner and Shared Facilities Manager, and (g) compensate the other Owner for its Net Revenue Loss as a result of lost generation due to an outage or disconnection of such Owner's Project. Any Owner connecting its own Project to the Shared Facilities, shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Owner from all Liabilities, including third party claims, property and revenue losses incurred, related to such construction or installation activities, but such installing Owner may seek reimbursement for such indemnified costs from insurance required by Section 12 to the extent such insurance provides coverage for such indemnified costs. 6. USE OF SHARED FACILITIES. 6.1 Shared Facilities Representatives. Each Owner shall, by written notice to the other Owners and Shared Facilities Manager, designate an individual (the "Shared Facilities Representative"), who will have authority to bind the Owner in all matters concerning this Agreement, to communicate on a day-to-day basis with the other Owner and to direct Shared Facilities Manager regarding construction, operations and maintenance issues. Each Owner may change its Shared Facilities Representative at any time and from time to time by prior written notice to the other Owners and Shared Facilities Manager. 6.2 Liens. Neither the Shared Facilities Manager nor any Owner shall, directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any Lien on the Shared Facilities, including but not Page 6 Cotenancy and Shared Facililies Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Poinl Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956. 5 limited to Liens for taxes (other than Permitted Liens), judgments, construction work, repair and restoration, or materials furnished, other than Permitted Liens. The Shared Facilities Manager and each Owner shall take prompt steps to discharge any Lien filed against any of the Shared Facilities, other than a Permitted Lien. If the Shared Facilities Manager or the Owner responsible for the imposition of a Lien fails to discharge promptly any such Lien, the other Parties, in addition to any other rights it may have at law or equity for a breach of this Agreement, shall have the right to notify the responsible Owner in writing and to take any reasonable action to satisfy, defend, settle or otherwise remove the Lien at the responsible Party's expense. 6.3 Curtailment of Delivery. The Owners shall interrupt or reduce deliveries of electrical power over the Shared Facilities if requested to do so by the Shared Facilities Manager in accordance with the following provisions: (i) after reasonable notice to, and agreement by, Owners as to the timing and duration of the curtailment, to maintain, repair, replace, remove, investigate, inspect or test any part of the Shared Facilities in accordance with the terms of this Agreement; (ii) if the interruption or reduction is necessary due to an Emergency, or (iii) if the Shared Facilities Manager is ordered to do so by the Transmission Provider, any other Governmental Authority or regulatory authority with jurisdiction over their Shared Facilities, or an Owner (or its authorized agent) notifies the Shared Facilities Manager that such curtailment is required by the Transmission Provider or another Governmental Authority or regulatory authority with jurisdiction over their Shared Facilities. The Shared Facilities Manager shall limit the length of any such interruption or curtailment to that time strictly necessary to correct the problem. Any interruption or curtailment made pursuant to clause (i) above shall be made to the extent commercially reasonable during periods that minimize potential loss of revenue of the Owner(s) being curtailed. Unless directed otherwise by the Transmission Provider, the Transmission Owner or any other Governmental Authority or regulatory authority with jurisdiction over the Shared Facilities, the Shared Facilities Manager shall work with the Owners to allocate curtailment orders issued under sub-clauses (ii) and (iii) of the first sentence of this Section 6.3 among Owners as follows: (a) to the extent such curtailment order is specific to a Project or Projects, the curtailment shall be allocated entirely to such Project or Projects in accordance with the curtailment order; or (b) to the extent such curtailment order is not specific to a Project or Projects, the curtailment shall be allocated among the Projects that would otherwise have been producing more energy during the curtailment period but for the curtailment on a pro rata based on the ratio of each Project's Reserved Capacity to the aggregate Reserved Capacity of all Projects; provided, however, that if an allocation is made by Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to clause (b) above, then the Parties acknowledge that such allocation will be as close to the formula described above as Shared Facilities Manager can accomplish, acting commercially reasonably. To the extent any curtailment is caused by any specific Project(s) or a breach by any specific Owner(s) of its obligations hereunder or by the action or inaction of any individual Owner or Owners, the Owner or Owners who owns such specific Project(s), whose breach of its obligations hereunder or whose action or inaction caused the curtailment shall reimburse the other Owners for Page 7 Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956.5 all Net Revenue Losses suffered by them arising from such curtailment, it being hereby agreed that payment of the Net Revenue Losses shall be the affected Owner's sole and exclusive remedy against such other Owner with respect to any losses due to such curtailment. The Parties agree that the actual losses arising between and among themselves due to such curtailment would be difficult to compute and that the methodology for determining such losses set forth above is a good faith estimate of the calculations utilized to determine the actual losses that would be suffered. 7. OBLIGATIONS AND CERTAIN RIGHTS OF THE OWNERS. 7 .1 Standards of Performance. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement to the contrary, each Owner will develop, construct, operate and maintain its Project and perform its obligations under this Agreement in accordance with (a) all applicable Laws and Governmental Approvals, (b) Prudent Industry Practices, (c) the Interconnection Agreements, (d) applicable terms of the Shared Premises Agreements, and (e) the applicable power purchase agreement of each respective Owner. No Owner will take any action, omit to take any action or fail to perform any obligation under this Agreement, the Shared Premises Agreements, the Interconnection Agreement, Governmental Approvals, or power purchase agreements, that materially and adversely affects any other Owner or another Owner's Project or gives rise to a Liability affecting any other Owner, another Owner's Project, or the Shared Facilities, including any action, omission or failure to perform an obligation that results in damage to, disconnection of, or an outage of another Owner's Project. 7 .2 Taxes. The Shared Facilities Manager shall pay all real and personal property Taxes, general or special, levied against the Shared Facilities and the Owners' interests in the Shared Premises before delinquency and before any fine, interest or penalty will become due or be imposed for their non-payment, except that the Shared Facilities Manager may withhold payment of any Tax if Shared Facilities Manager is contesting the payment of such Tax in good faith by appropriate proceedings and such proceeding does not involve any danger of the sale, forfeiture or loss of any part of such Shared Facilities or interest in the Shared Premises, including the posting of any bond that is required by applicable Law to avoid such sale, forfeiture or loss while the payment of such Tax is being contested and notifies all the Owners thereof in writing at least thirty (30) days before such payment is due. All such Taxes and assessments paid by the Shared Facilities Manager shall be treated as Shared Expenses and invoiced to the Owners in 7 .3 Environmental Compliance. Each Owner shall, with respect to its Project, (including its Project Specific Assets, including the Project Site upon which its Project is installed), be responsible for and shall have exclusive control over all investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action required by (i) any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters, or (ii) any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to such Owner's use, operation or ownership of its Project (including its Project Specific Assets and Project Site). The Shared Facilities Manager shall, with respect to the Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities located on the Shared Premises oversee all investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate Page8 Cotenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC) 4853-2776-3956.5 environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to the Owners' use of the Shared Premises or the Shared Facilities located on the Shared Premises, and subject to Sections 11. l and 11.2, each Owner shall be responsible, in proportion to its relative Project Percentage Interest, for all Liabilities related to such investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action. Shared Facilities Manager shall keep all Owners fully appraised as to the above matters affecting the Shared Premises and shall consult with all of them prior to taking any action involving any Governmental Authority or risk of incurring any Liability. 7.4 Interconnection. Each Owner shall be solely responsible for securing for its own benefit, and for maintaining, such rights as are necessary to interconnect its Project with the transmission and interconnection system controlled by the Transmission Provider and to deliver the electrical energy generated by its Project, or such portion of the electrical energy generated by its Project, as is consistent with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. For the avoidance of doubt, each Owner will separately deliver and meter the electrical energy generated by its Project and delivered to the Shared Facilities. 7.5 Relationship of the Owners. The rights, duties, obligations and Liabilities of the Owners under this Agreement will be individual and not joint or collective, and no Owner shall be responsible for the default of any other Owner under this Agreement. It is not the intention of the Owners to create, nor will this Agreement be deemed to create, any partnership, agency, joint venture, trust, or association of profit, or to authorize any Owner to act as an agent, servant or employee for any other Owner. Each Owner will remain solely responsible for the actions of its own employees. Regulatory Status. 7.6.1 Each Owner represents and warrants that it is or will be an EWG at all times while it is operating the Project owned by it, and each Owner covenants to maintain its status as an EWG for so long as it is operating its Project and is a Party to this Agreement. No Owner will take any action that could adversely impact any other Owner's ability to qualify as an EWG. 7.6.2 With respect to any Transfers after the Effective Date, any required FERC approvals under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act will be obtained prior to the effective date of the transfer of ownership of any FERC-jurisdictional facilities. 7.6.3 This Agreement shall be filed with FERC for its acceptance or approval under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act. 7.7 No Dedication of Property: No Public Access. Each Owner agrees that entering into this Agreement, performing its obligations hereunder, or exercising its rights hereunder, either in whole or part, is not intended to be, and shall in no way be construed as or deemed to be a dedication to public or quasi-public use or purpose of any of the Project Specific Assets of the Owner, the Project Specific Assets of another Owner, any Shared Facilities or Shared Premises, or any portion of the foregoing. The Owners undertake to cooperate in enforcing such requirement Page 9 Colenancy and Shared Facilities Agreemem (EcoGrove Wind LLC -High Point Solar LLC> 4853-2776-3956.5 for limiting physical access to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, including permitting Shared Facilities Manager to establish and enforce procedures and protocol for security, safety, and protection of the Shared Facilities. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Parties shall comply with requirements set forth in any Governmental Approvals. 7 .8 Crossing and Co-location Rights. Each Owner hereunder shall be permitted to cross and encroach upon the Shared Premises with its Project Specific Assets solely to the extent necessary to develop, construct, operate and maintain its Project, provided that any such crossings, encroachments, or overhang shall be subject to the noninterference and overburdening protections of Section 5.3 above. In particular, any Owner's exercise of rights under this Section 7.8 shall only be permitted in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices and the Shared Premises Agreements, and shall not interfere with or endanger the construction, operation, or maintenance of the Shared Facilities or other facilities already in place on the Shared Premises. In the event of a conflict in the location or operation of the Shared Facilities and any Project Specific Assets on the Shared Premises, the Shared Facilities shall take priority over the Project Specific Assets, and any Project Specific Assets existing within the Shared Premises shall take priority over any subsequent Project Specific Assets requiring the use of the Shared Premises. 7.9 Co-location of Transmission Owner Monitoring and Control Facilities. The Owners acknowledge and agree that the Transmission Owner may require the use of the Shared Premises for the co-location of certain control, metering, and monitoring equipment servicing the Projects. Shared Facilities Manager may in its sole discretion grant the Transmission Owner that access needed for such activities. 7 .10 Cooperation. record_data.record_plain_text: EcoGrove Wind LLC FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF NO. 1 1. Availability. EcoGrove Wind LLC ("Seller") makes energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale, except as prohibited in 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, Section 35.39(b). 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all of Seller's sales of energy and capacity not otherwise subject to a particular tariff of Seller. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at the rates established between the purchaser and the Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller has requested and been granted the following waivers of Commission regulations, pursuant to a Letter Order issued by the Commission in EcoGrove Wind, LLC, Docket No. ER09-554-000 (Mar. 6, 2009) (unpublished letter order): (a) authorization for sales of energy at market-based rates; (b) waiver of the filing requirements of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, 18 C.F.R. Part 35 (except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16); (c) waiver of the accounting , reporting and other requirements of 18 C.F.R. Parts 41 (accounts, records and memoranda), 101 (uniform system of accounts) and 141 (statement and reports); (d) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act and 18 C.F.R. Part 34 for any future securities or debt issuances or assumption of liabilities by Seller; and (e) such other waivers and authorizations as the Commission may deem appropriate. 7. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 2 Seller in the Northeast region and a Category 1 Seller in the Southeast, Central, Southwest, Southwest Power Pool, and Northwest regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). 8. Effective Date. This Tariff is effective on such date as set by the Commission.
